{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "When you glance at the weather app and see '70% chance of rain,' you're reading probability in action. That number shapes whether you grab an umbrella, reschedule your picnic, or risk it and dash between raindrops.",
      "title": "Checking the Weather App"
    },
    {
      "text": "Insurance companies bet on probability every day. They calculate the likelihood you'll file a claim and set your premium accordingly. The safer your profile, the lower their risk — and the less you pay each month.",
      "title": "Your Car Insurance Premium"
    },
    {
      "text": "Fantasy sports players live and die by probability. Choosing a quarterback means weighing completion rates, injury history, and matchups — all informal probability estimates — to maximize your weekly score.",
      "title": "Fantasy Sports Draft Night"
    },
    {
      "text": "Casinos are built on probability. Every slot machine, blackjack table, and roulette wheel is engineered so the house wins slightly more often than players. That small edge, repeated millions of times, is pure profit.",
      "title": "The Casino Floor"
    },
    {
      "text": "When a doctor says 'this medication works in 8 out of 10 patients,' they're giving you a probability. You and your doctor weigh that number against side effect risks to decide whether the treatment is worth pursuing.",
      "title": "A Doctor's Recommendation"
    },
    {
      "text": "Retailers use probability to manage shelves. If historical data shows 90% of customers buy milk on weekends, stores stock extra before Saturday. Running out is costly — overstocking is too. Probability finds the sweet spot.",
      "title": "Grocery Store Stocking"
    },
    {
      "text": "Every time Netflix recommends a show, an algorithm has estimated the probability you'll enjoy it based on your watch history. That 'Because you watched...' row is a ranked list of likelihoods tailored just for you.",
      "title": "Netflix Recommendations"
    },
    {
      "text": "Poker players don't just play cards — they play probabilities. Knowing there are 13 hearts in a 52-card deck, a player calculates the chance of hitting a flush and decides whether the pot is worth the gamble.",
      "title": "Poker Table Decisions"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Flight prices spike during spring break and holidays — not because airlines changed anything, but because millions of people want the same seats at once. Demand surges, supply stays fixed, and prices climb until fewer people are willing to pay.",
      "title": "Booking a Flight Home"
    },
    {
      "text": "That PS5 launch in 2020? Factories couldn't keep up with millions of eager buyers. Shelves emptied in hours, scalpers resold consoles for triple the price, and the shortage lasted months — a textbook demand surge meeting a supply crunch.",
      "title": "Console Launch Day Chaos"
    },
    {
      "text": "Uber prices jump during a rainstorm because everyone wants a ride at the same moment while driver supply stays the same. That 'surge pricing' notification is literally supply and demand recalculating the equilibrium price in real time.",
      "title": "Surge Pricing on a Rainy Night"
    },
    {
      "text": "A drought destroys wheat crops across major farming regions. Less wheat reaches markets, bakeries pay more for flour, and bread prices rise at your grocery store — even though your local weather was fine.",
      "title": "Why Your Bread Got Pricier"
    },
    {
      "text": "Concert tickets for a beloved reunion tour sell out in minutes at face value, then reappear on StubHub for 10x the price. The original venue had fixed supply; demand wildly exceeded it, creating a secondary market at the new equilibrium.",
      "title": "Resale Tickets Gone Wild"
    },
    {
      "text": "When electric vehicles became trendy, lithium prices skyrocketed because battery production suddenly needed far more of it than mines could supply. One industry's demand shift rippled through an entire global supply chain.",
      "title": "The EV Battery Rush"
    },
    {
      "text": "Avocado toast went mainstream around 2015, and avocado prices surged globally. Farmers responded by planting more trees — but trees take years to mature, so supply couldn't catch up quickly, keeping prices elevated for a long stretch.",
      "title": "The Avocado Boom"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Ever stared at a Matryoshka doll? Open one and there's a smaller doll inside. Open that one — another. Each doll is the same pattern, just smaller. That's recursion living in your hands, not on a screen.",
      "title": "Russian Nesting Dolls"
    },
    {
      "text": "Mirrors facing each other in a barbershop create an infinite hallway of reflections — each reflection containing another, smaller reflection. You're literally standing inside a recursive structure every time you get a haircut.",
      "title": "The Barbershop Mirror Trick"
    },
    {
      "text": "Google's search suggests completions. Each suggestion, if clicked, triggers a new search that spawns new suggestions. Autocomplete menus, folder trees, comment threads with replies to replies — your browser is full of recursion.",
      "title": "Your Browser, Every Day"
    },
    {
      "text": "When Sherlock Holmes solves a case, he breaks it into smaller mysteries: Who had motive? Break that down further. Who had access? Each sub-question mirrors the original. Detectives — real and fictional — think recursively.",
      "title": "How Detectives Think"
    },
    {
      "text": "Zoom into a coastline on a map. The jagged edges look the same at every scale — bays contain smaller bays, peninsulas contain smaller peninsulas. These fractal shapes are nature's recursion, appearing in snowflakes, ferns, and lightning bolts.",
      "title": "Fractals in Nature"
    },
    {
      "text": "In chess engines and strategy games like StarCraft, AI plans moves by thinking: 'If I do X, they'll do Y, then I'll do Z...' Each hypothetical triggers another. The AI recurses through decision trees millions of times per second.",
      "title": "Video Game AI Strategies"
    },
    {
      "text": "Pixar's animators build recursive algorithms to simulate hair, fur, and cloth. Each fiber reacts to the ones around it, which react back, cascading through the simulation — millions of recursive interactions creating realistic movement.",
      "title": "Pixar's Animation Magic"
    },
    {
      "text": "When you sort a pile of papers, you might split them into two piles, sort each pile, then merge. If each sub-pile gets split again, you're running merge sort — the same recursive algorithm computers use — without even realizing it.",
      "title": "Sorting Papers at Your Desk"
    },
    {
      "text": "Legal systems reference themselves constantly: a law may cite another law that cites a precedent that references the original statute. Constitutional lawyers navigate deeply recursive document structures every day in practice.",
      "title": "Law Books Citing Law Books"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Você pesquisa um tênis, fecha o site, e de repente ele aparece em todo lugar: no Instagram, no YouTube, nos anúncios do jornal. Não é perseguição — é o viés de frequência. Você só passou a notar o que já estava na sua cabeça.",
      "title": "O Tênis Que Te Segue"
    },
    {
      "text": "O primeiro preço que você vê numa loja vira âncora. Um sofá de R$5.000 'com desconto' por R$3.200 parece barato — mas só em comparação com o valor inflado. Seu cérebro usa o número inicial como referência, mesmo que seja arbitrário.",
      "title": "Desconto ou Armadilha?"
    },
    {
      "text": "Você conhece alguém simpático numa festa e assume que ele é também honesto, inteligente e confiável. O efeito halo faz uma característica positiva contaminar toda a percepção. Funciona ao contrário também: um deslize e tudo parece suspeito.",
      "title": "Amor à Primeira Vista (de Caráter)"
    },
    {
      "text": "No feed político, você curte, comenta e compartilha quem concorda com você. O algoritmo aprende e te mostra mais do mesmo. Resultado: você acha que 'todo mundo pensa assim' — mas só está vendo um pedaço cuidadosamente filtrado da realidade.",
      "title": "Sua Bolha Política Online"
    },
    {
      "text": "Seu time perdeu porque o juiz foi péssimo. Mas quando ganhou, foi porque jogou bem. O viés de atribuição aparece toda vez que explicamos nossos fracassos por fatores externos e nossos sucessos por mérito próprio.",
      "title": "Futebol e Desculpas Clássicas"
    },
    {
      "text": "Você já pagou academia por meses sem ir porque 'já gastei, seria um desperdício cancelar'. Isso é a falácia do custo irrecuperável — continuar investindo tempo, dinheiro ou energia em algo só porque já investiu antes.",
      "title": "A Academia Que Você Não Frequenta"
    },
    {
      "text": "Numa reunião, a primeira pessoa a falar define o tom da discussão. Os outros tendem a ajustar suas opiniões ao redor da ideia inicial, mesmo sem perceber. Líderes experientes sabem disso e usam a ordem de fala estrategicamente.",
      "title": "Quem Fala Primeiro, Manda"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Cuando los médicos te recetan antibióticos, insisten en que termines el tratamiento completo. Si paras antes, las bacterias más resistentes sobreviven y se reproducen. En años, tienes infecciones que ya no responden a los mismos medicamentos.",
      "title": "Bacterias que escapan a los antibióticos"
    },
    {
      "text": "Los mosquitos en zonas donde se usó DDT por décadas son ahora casi inmunes a ese insecticida. Los que sobrevivieron la exposición inicial transmitieron esa resistencia, y hoy esa población entera la porta.",
      "title": "Mosquitos resistentes a insecticidas"
    },
    {
      "text": "Los perros que ves hoy — bulldogs, pastores alemanes, chihuahuas — son lobos moldeados por siglos de selección humana. Elegimos quién se reproducía según utilidad o apariencia, acelerando el mismo proceso que ocurre en la naturaleza.",
      "title": "Razas de perros: evolución acelerada"
    },
    {
      "text": "En el océano, los peces más coloridos o de tamaño ideal para el mercado son capturados primero. Los que quedan y se reproducen son los más pequeños o menos llamativos. La pesca comercial está cambiando la evolución de especies marinas en tiempo real.",
      "title": "La pesca cambia a los peces"
    },
    {
      "text": "Durante la Revolución Industrial en Inglaterra, las polillas blancas se volvieron oscuras en décadas porque el hollín ennegrecía los árboles. Las oscuras se camuflaban mejor, sobrevivían más y dominaron la población. Hoy es un ícono de selección natural observable.",
      "title": "Polillas y la Revolución Industrial"
    },
    {
      "text": "El VIH muta tan rápido que los medicamentos que funcionaban hace diez años ya no sirven solos. Los virólogos combinan varios fármacos precisamente para que el virus no pueda evolucionar resistencia a todos al mismo tiempo.",
      "title": "El VIH evoluciona dentro de ti"
    },
    {
      "text": "Las ciudades crean ambientes nuevos y los animales responden. Palomas, zorros urbanos y hasta peces en ríos contaminados están desarrollando rasgos distintos a sus primos rurales — tolerancia al ruido, dietas diferentes, ciclos de sueño alterados.",
      "title": "Animales que se adaptan a las ciudades"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "That \"You might also like\" row on Netflix isn't a human curator — it's a machine learning model that has studied your watch history, pause points, and ratings to predict what you'll enjoy next.",
      "title": "Netflix Knows Your Taste"
    },
    {
      "text": "Every time Gmail moves an email to Spam, ML is at work. It has processed millions of messages to recognize patterns like suspicious links, urgent money requests, and unfamiliar senders — all without a human reviewing each one.",
      "title": "Your Spam Folder"
    },
    {
      "text": "Say \"Hey Siri\" or \"OK Google\" and ML converts your spoken words into text in real time. It has learned from countless voice recordings to handle accents, background noise, and even your mumbling.",
      "title": "Voice Assistants Listening"
    },
    {
      "text": "Unlock your phone with your face and you're using ML that maps dozens of facial points — the distance between your eyes, the shape of your jaw — to confirm it's really you, even in dim lighting.",
      "title": "Face Unlock on Your Phone"
    },
    {
      "text": "Google Maps doesn't just know speed limits — it learns from millions of drivers moving through the same roads right now to predict whether your commute will take 18 minutes or 42 minutes today.",
      "title": "Traffic Predictions on Maps"
    },
    {
      "text": "Those targeted ads that seem to read your mind? An ML model analyzed your browsing history, location, and purchase patterns to predict which products you're most likely to click on or buy.",
      "title": "Ads That Know You Too Well"
    },
    {
      "text": "When your bank texts \"Unusual activity detected,\" ML flagged a purchase that didn't fit your normal spending patterns — location, amount, and timing all looked different from your history.",
      "title": "Fraud Alerts from Your Bank"
    },
    {
      "text": "Instagram and TikTok don't show posts in chronological order. ML ranks every piece of content against your past behavior — what you liked, rewatched, or scrolled past — to keep you engaged longer.",
      "title": "Social Media Feeds"
    },
    {
      "text": "Photo apps automatically tag \"Beach Trip 2023\" without you labeling anything. ML recognizes sand, water, and sunlight in your pictures the same way it learned to recognize cats — from millions of examples.",
      "title": "Auto-Tagged Photo Albums"
    },
    {
      "text": "When Spotify builds your Discover Weekly playlist, ML cross-references your listening habits with users who share similar tastes — finding music you've never heard but are statistically likely to love.",
      "title": "Spotify's Discover Weekly"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "That $5 daily coffee habit costs more than $1,825 a year. But invested at 7% annually, it becomes over $75,000 in 30 years. Compounding turns tiny daily choices into life-changing sums — in either direction.",
      "title": "Your Morning Coffee, Reimagined"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your 401(k) isn't just growing from new paycheck contributions. Last year's investment gains are now earning their own returns. A portfolio that felt slow in year 5 starts visibly accelerating by year 20 — that's compounding showing up to work.",
      "title": "Your Retirement Account at Work"
    },
    {
      "text": "That $3,000 credit card balance at 24% APR? Left unpaid, it nearly doubles in 3 years — not because of new purchases, but because interest charges accumulate interest of their own. Compounding works against you just as powerfully as it works for you.",
      "title": "The Credit Card Trap"
    },
    {
      "text": "Amazon, Apple, and Tesla didn't grow linearly. Reinvested profits funded more growth, which funded even more. What looked like explosive overnight success was often decades of compounding business momentum finally becoming impossible to ignore.",
      "title": "How Big Companies Got Huge"
    },
    {
      "text": "Sports dynasties compound too. Championship experience attracts better recruits, who win more games, which build stronger reputations. Teams like the Golden State Warriors didn't just add talent — they compounded cultural and competitive advantages year over year.",
      "title": "Dynasty Teams in Sports"
    },
    {
      "text": "Learning a skill compounds. The Spanish you learned last month makes this month's lessons easier to absorb. Musicians who practice daily don't just add notes — they compound pattern recognition, muscle memory, and musical intuition simultaneously.",
      "title": "Skill Building Over Time"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your reputation compounds quietly. Each delivered project, helpful favor, or respected opinion adds to a professional credibility that attracts more opportunities — which build even more credibility. LinkedIn connections snowball because trust compounds just like interest.",
      "title": "Reputation in Your Career"
    },
    {
      "text": "Climate scientists track compounding in melting ice sheets: less ice means less sunlight reflected, which means more warming, which melts more ice. Compounding isn't just a finance concept — it's a pattern that accelerates change across natural systems too.",
      "title": "Compounding in Climate Science"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Cada mordida no pão, arroz ou salada existe porque uma planta capturou luz solar. A fotossíntese transformou energia do sol em açúcares que viram grãos, frutas e folhas — tudo que você coloca no prato tem essa origem.",
      "title": "O que há no seu prato"
    },
    {
      "text": "Quando você respira fundo numa floresta ou parque, está aproveitando o oxigênio liberado por milhões de plantas ao redor. Cada árvore que você vê é uma pequena usina produzindo o ar que mantém você vivo agora mesmo.",
      "title": "O ar que você respira agora"
    },
    {
      "text": "As florestas tropicais, como a Amazônia, são chamadas de 'pulmão do planeta' justamente porque absorvem bilhões de toneladas de CO2 por ano. Sem a fotossíntese em larga escala, o efeito estufa seria muito mais intenso.",
      "title": "Amazônia e o clima global"
    },
    {
      "text": "Gasolina, carvão e gás natural são energia solar armazenada por fotossíntese há milhões de anos. Plantas antigas capturaram luz, morreram, e viraram combustível. Você literalmente dirige com luz solar fossilizada.",
      "title": "Combustíveis fósseis no seu carro"
    },
    {
      "text": "Em aquários e oceanos, algas microscópicas fazem fotossíntese e produzem mais da metade do oxigênio do planeta. A cada dois respiros seus, um foi presente do oceano — não das árvores.",
      "title": "O oceano que te mantém vivo"
    },
    {
      "text": "Agricultores escolhem culturas, horários de plantio e espaçamento entre plantas pensando em maximizar a captação de luz solar. Toda decisão numa fazenda moderna leva em conta como otimizar a fotossíntese.",
      "title": "Fazendas e luz solar"
    },
    {
      "text": "Pesquisadores tentam replicar a fotossíntese artificialmente para criar energia limpa. Painéis solares são uma versão tecnológica dessa ideia — capturar luz e transformá-la em algo útil, assim como as plantas fazem há bilhões de anos.",
      "title": "Energia solar inspirada nas plantas"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Cuando escribes tu contraseña en Gmail o Outlook, la encriptación la convierte en código ilegible antes de viajar por internet. Nadie que intercepte esa señal puede leer tus mensajes — solo el servidor destino tiene la clave para descifrarlos.",
      "title": "Tu Correo Electrónico"
    },
    {
      "text": "Cada vez que pagas con tarjeta en Amazon, Mercado Libre o cualquier tienda online, la encriptación protege tus datos bancarios en tránsito. El proceso ocurre en milisegundos — tú compras, ella trabaja silenciosamente de fondo.",
      "title": "Compras en Línea"
    },
    {
      "text": "WhatsApp y Telegram usan encriptación de extremo a extremo. Ni siquiera la empresa puede leer tus chats. Cada conversación viaja empaquetada en un código que solo tú y tu contacto pueden abrir.",
      "title": "Mensajes de WhatsApp"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tu banco encripta cada transacción: transferencias, consultas de saldo, pagos de servicios. El candado que ves en el navegador al entrar a tu banca en línea es tu señal visual de que está protegido.",
      "title": "Banca Desde Tu Celular"
    },
    {
      "text": "Las plataformas de streaming como Netflix encriptan el video que ves para evitar piratería y proteger tu cuenta. Tu contraseña de suscripción también viaja encriptada cada vez que inicias sesión.",
      "title": "Netflix y Streaming"
    },
    {
      "text": "iCloud, Google Drive y Dropbox encriptan tus fotos y documentos almacenados. Incluso si alguien accediera a los servidores físicamente, los archivos serían ilegibles sin las claves correctas.",
      "title": "Tus Archivos en la Nube"
    },
    {
      "text": "Los iPhones y teléfonos Android modernos encriptan todo su almacenamiento interno. Si alguien roba tu celular y extrae el chip de memoria, solo verá datos incomprensibles sin tu PIN o huella digital.",
      "title": "El Celular en Tu Bolsillo"
    },
    {
      "text": "Las redes WiFi con contraseña usan protocolos como WPA3 para encriptar el tráfico entre tu dispositivo y el router. Por eso conectarte a WiFi público sin VPN es más riesgoso — algunos no encriptan bien.",
      "title": "WiFi de Tu Casa"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Your body runs on invisible thermostats. When you overheat during a run, you sweat to cool down. When blood sugar spikes after a meal, insulin kicks in to lower it. Your biology is a network of stabilizing loops keeping you in the zone.",
      "title": "Your Body's Built-In Thermostats"
    },
    {
      "text": "Ever notice how a trending tweet keeps getting shared? More visibility brings more engagement, which boosts visibility further. Social media algorithms are amplifying feedback loops — the popular gets more popular, fast.",
      "title": "Trending Is a Feedback Loop"
    },
    {
      "text": "Wildfires create their own weather. Heat dries out surrounding vegetation, giving the fire more fuel, which grows the heat. Fires literally feed themselves through a runaway amplifying loop — nature's version of a screech.",
      "title": "Wildfires That Feed Themselves"
    },
    {
      "text": "Housing prices in desirable cities rise as people move there. That attracts more investment and development, which signals desirability, pulling more people in. Entire real estate markets spiral through self-reinforcing feedback.",
      "title": "Real Estate Price Spirals"
    },
    {
      "text": "Learning a skill builds confidence. Confidence pushes you to practice more. More practice improves skill further. Athletes, musicians, and coders all ride this same amplifying loop — the more you do, the more capable you become.",
      "title": "Confidence & Skill Building"
    },
    {
      "text": "Glacier melt exposes darker ocean water, which absorbs more heat than ice, warming the region faster, melting more glaciers. Climate scientists track these amplifying loops because they can tip slowly into sudden acceleration.",
      "title": "Melting Ice & Climate Loops"
    },
    {
      "text": "Stock markets panic when prices drop. Investors sell, prices drop further, triggering more selling. Market crashes aren't just math — they're amplifying feedback loops in collective human behavior.",
      "title": "Market Crashes & Panic Selling"
    },
    {
      "text": "Good sleep improves your mood and focus. Better focus helps you exercise and eat well. That reduces stress, which improves sleep quality. Small lifestyle habits lock together into stabilizing loops you barely have to think about.",
      "title": "Sleep, Mood & Healthy Habits"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "That $5 daily latte isn't just $5 — it's also whatever you'd have bought instead. But zoom out: $150/month could be a gym membership, a streaming service, and savings. Every swipe reveals a silent trade-off.",
      "title": "Your Morning Coffee Run"
    },
    {
      "text": "Scrolling Instagram for 45 minutes before bed? The hidden cost isn't just sleep — it's the book chapter you didn't read, the language app you skipped, or the journal entry that never happened. Attention is currency.",
      "title": "The Late-Night Scroll"
    },
    {
      "text": "A hiring manager choosing between two candidates isn't just picking one person — they're permanently passing on the other. Every 'yes' in business is a quiet 'no' to every alternative use of that salary budget.",
      "title": "The Job Offer Decision"
    },
    {
      "text": "Netflix added a show you love — but so did two other platforms. Subscribing to all three means giving up $30/month you could've used elsewhere. Streaming wars are really a battle for your opportunity cost.",
      "title": "Too Many Streaming Services"
    },
    {
      "text": "Elite athletes train 6 hours daily. The hidden cost isn't just exhaustion — it's college parties skipped, careers delayed, relationships deprioritized. Their medals represent thousands of foregone alternatives.",
      "title": "The Olympian's Real Sacrifice"
    },
    {
      "text": "Buying a house locks up your down payment. That $60,000 sitting in equity isn't earning stock market returns. Homeowners unknowingly trade investment flexibility for stability — whether they realize it or not.",
      "title": "Owning a Home"
    },
    {
      "text": "Saying yes to a friend's favor on Saturday afternoon silently cancels your workout, your errands, and your quiet recharge time. Every social commitment carries an invisible price tag of alternative uses of your day.",
      "title": "Helping a Friend Move"
    },
    {
      "text": "Doctors who leave medicine to start companies aren't just changing jobs — they're calculating that entrepreneurship's potential outweighs years of medical school investment AND future earnings. A massive hidden trade-off made visible.",
      "title": "The Career Switcher"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Quando você abre o e-mail esperando uma boa notícia ou checa o celular aguardando uma resposta importante, a dopamina já está agindo — antes mesmo de qualquer recompensa chegar. É a antecipação que te mantém olhando a tela.",
      "title": "Checando o Celular"
    },
    {
      "text": "Curtidas, comentários e compartilhamentos são o combustível das redes sociais. Cada notificação é uma mini-recompensa que dispara dopamina. Não é coincidência que você fica rolando o feed mesmo sem querer — o sistema foi projetado para isso.",
      "title": "Redes Sociais e Notificações"
    },
    {
      "text": "Jogos como Fortnite ou Candy Crush entregam recompensas variáveis: às vezes você ganha, às vezes perde. Essa imprevisibilidade dispara picos de dopamina maiores do que recompensas garantidas — é o mesmo princípio das máquinas caça-níqueis.",
      "title": "Games e Recompensas Variáveis"
    },
    {
      "text": "Cada item riscado da sua lista de tarefas libera uma dose de dopamina. Por isso tantas pessoas adoram fazer listas — e até adicionam tarefas já feitas só para riscar. O cérebro recompensa o senso de progresso.",
      "title": "Listas de Tarefas"
    },
    {
      "text": "Quando você começa uma série nova e para no cliffhanger do episódio, a dopamina te empurra para o próximo. O 'mais um episódio' das plataformas de streaming é dopamina trabalhando a seu favor — ou contra o seu sono.",
      "title": "Maratonas de Séries"
    },
    {
      "text": "Comprar algo novo, mesmo que pequeno, ativa o sistema de recompensa. O pico muitas vezes ocorre antes da compra, durante a busca e a decisão. É por isso que pesquisar produtos às vezes é mais prazeroso do que receber o pacote.",
      "title": "O Prazer das Compras"
    },
    {
      "text": "Metas de corrida, recordes pessoais na academia ou subir de nível num esporte — atletas amadores vivem esse ciclo. A dopamina reforça o hábito de treinar ao associar esforço com a satisfação de superar limites.",
      "title": "Esportes e Metas Pessoais"
    },
